# help/en/overview.ftl — FreeSynergy Default Icons help texts (English)

help-freesynergy-default-icons-title = FreeSynergy Default Icon Set

help-freesynergy-default-icons-body =
    The FreeSynergy Default icon set is the official icon library for the platform.
    All icons are scalable SVGs drawn in a clean modern line style. They adapt their
    stroke color to the active desktop theme, so they look correct on Midnight Blue,
    Nordic Dark, Cloud White, and any custom theme.

    Icon categories:
    - apps — application launcher icons for all installed packages
    - actions — verbs: save, delete, copy, move, upload, download, ...
    - status — indicators: running, stopped, warning, error, syncing, ...
    - mimetypes — file type icons (documents, images, audio, video, archives, ...)
    - devices — storage, printers, network interfaces, cameras, ...
    - places — folders, home, trash, network locations, ...

    This set is installed by default and is selected automatically unless another
    icon set is installed and set as active.

help-freesynergy-default-icons-switching-title = Switching Icon Sets

help-freesynergy-default-icons-switching-body =
    To install an alternative icon set:
    1. Open the Store and browse to Icons.
    2. Install the desired icon set package.
    3. Open Desktop Settings > Appearance > Icons.
    4. Select the new icon set from the dropdown.
    5. Changes take effect immediately — no logout required.

    The FreeSynergy Default set is always available as a fallback. If an installed
    icon set does not include an icon for a particular action or MIME type, the
    FreeSynergy Default icon is used automatically.
